Norm MacDonald came up with the idea for "Celebrity Jeopardy."  It was based on the fact that, as Norm pointed out in an interview, they make game shows "really easy" for celebrities. It was also based on an old SCTV "Jeopardy"-style sketch using really dumb people. Norm asked Martin Short who wrote that sketch so he could get permission to do it on SNL without being accused of stealing, so Norm called up Eugene Levy and got his permission. Norm also loves the word "Chinaman," because he thinks is funny and "the least racist, racial insult."
